  "description": [
    "THE IMPORTANCE OF A STENO ORAPHICAL EDUCATION A progressive principle is pro C pelling us onward and upward Improvement follows improvement and one of the greatest improve ments of the age is the short meth od of writing as taught in the study of stenography In the old Gre cian days hieroglyphics were used resembling somewhat our present gvstem of shorthand though much more complicated Some of this writing was found when exeavat ing in the buried cities of the east but the shortband of the present day is that of which 1 wish to Fpeak For years the world has been trying to invent some rapid mode of writing which will answer all purposes aud save time to the thorough going business men and at last we have many systems of shorthand some of which it will take years to learn and others that can be mastered in a few months and thus enable the busy energetic man or woman to accomplish more work in one hour than they could with the ordinary longhand in ten leaving the re maining hours for other duties and for recreation Permit me to remark that the study of shorthand is highly fa"
